<h1>TEST - Bypass one character assumption</h1>

[[TEST(ARG)]] accepts an unevaluated expression as argument, and
returns a pattern bypasses SNOBOL4's one-character length assumption
(quickscan heuristics).

<aside>
<p>
It is never necessary to use [[TEST(ARG)]] with SPITBOL, because
SPITBOL does not have a one-character assumption.
</p>
</aside>

<H2>Uses</H2>
<A HREF="UNIQUE.html">UNIQUE</A>

<<INCLUDES>>=
-INCLUDE 'UNIQUE.INC'
@

<<TEST>>=
         DEFINE('TEST(ARG)NAME')			:(TEST_END)
*
TEST     IDENT(DATATYPE(ARG), 'EXPRESSION')                   :F(TEST_1)
         NAME = UNIQUE()
         $NAME = ARG
         TEST = EVAL("NULL $ *TEST('" NAME "')")               :(RETURN)
TEST_1   TEST = ?EVAL($ARG) .TEST_                 :S(NRETURN)F(FRETURN)
*
TEST_END
@

<<unit_test>>=
#!/usr/bin/bash
         exec "snobol4" "-b" "$0" "$@"
-INCLUDE 'TEST.INC'
         &CODE = 1
         &CODE = 0
END
@

